ssed his fortune through savvy real estate speculation. The house is now (in 2019) a bed-and-breakfast inn. It is one of four historic buildings, one on each corner of a Red Wing intersection", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020723673/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2020723674/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020723674/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2020723674/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2020723674/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2020723674/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.60171", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.60171", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/highsm.60171/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2020723674"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["highsmith, carol m."], "date": "2019-01-01", "dates": ["2019"], "description": ["1 photograph : digital, tiff file, color."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-08-31T04:13:05.226Z", "group": ["highsm", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "carol-m-highsmith", "main-catalog-split-01", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020723674/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/60100/60171_150px.jpg#h=106&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/60100/60171r.jpg#h=453&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/60100/60171v.jpg#h=724&w=1024"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["goodhue county", "minnesota", "united states", "red wing"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["online resource", "http://www.loc.gov/item/21813752", "2020723674", "2020-11-24t09:02:26"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["highsmith (carol m.) archive", "catalog", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "prints and photographs division"], "score": 38.191483, "shelf_id": "LC-DIG-highsm- 60171 (ONLINE) [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["color", "digital photographs", "houses", "red wing", "minnesota", "america", "lawther house", "goodhue county", "james lawther", "united states"], "timestamp": "2022-04-23T15:55:30.570Z", "title": "The historic Lawther House in Red Wing, Minnesota. James Lawther built his brick octagon in 1857. The unusual plan was purported to be both economical and beautiful, approaching nature's most ideal form, the sphere. Lawther came to Red Wing as a merchant but amassed his fortune through savvy real estate speculation. The house is now (in 2019) a bed-and-breakfast inn. It is one of four historic buildings, one on each corner of a Red Wing intersection", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020723674/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2020723676/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020723676/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2020723676/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2020723676/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2020723676/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.60173", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.60173", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/highsm.60173/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2020723676"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["highsmith, carol m."], "date": "2019-01-01", "dates": ["2019"], "description": ["1 photograph : digital, tiff file, color."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-08-31T02:09:50.117Z", "group": ["highsm", "catalog-split-03", "catalog", "carol-m-highsmith", "main-catalog-split-03", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020723676/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/60100/60173_150px.jpg#h=90&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/60100/60173r.jpg#h=383&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/60100/60173v.jpg#h=613&w=1024"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["goodhue county", "minnesota", "united states", "red wing"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["online resource", "2020-11-24t09:02:27", "2020723676", "http://www.loc.gov/item/21813754"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["highsmith (carol m.) archive", "catalog", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "prints and photographs division"], "score": 38.191483, "shelf_id": "LC-DIG-highsm- 60173 (ONLINE) [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["color", "digital photographs", "houses", "red wing", "minnesota", "america", "purcell feick and elmslie", "goodhue county", "prairie school style", "united states", "e.s. hoyt house"], "timestamp": "2022-04-23T15:55:30.570Z", "title": "The 1913 E.S. Hoyt House, one of the Purcell, Feick and Elmslie architectural firm's most successful Prairie School-style homes. The low-pitched roof and bands of leaded glass casement windows emphasize the broad horizontal lines of the house. Sawed wood designs ornament the house and the decorative screen shielding the garage passageway. The house is one of four historic buildings, one on each corner of a Red Wing intersection", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020723676/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2020723677/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020723677/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2020723677/", "https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2020723677/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/highsm/item/2020723677/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.60174", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.60174", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/highsm.60174/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2020723677"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["highsmith, carol m."], "date": "2019-01-01", "dates": ["2019"], "description": ["1 photograph : digital, tiff file, color."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-08-31T05:39:35.623Z", "group": ["highsm", "catalog-split-04", "catalog", "carol-m-highsmith", "