. Sawed wood designs ornament the house and the decorative screen shielding the garage passageway. The house is one of four historic buildings, one on each corner of a Red Wing intersection", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020723678/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01/data/sn89064422/00542865556/1930111401/0587.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01:data:sn89064422:00542865556:1930111401:0584/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01/data/sn89064422/00542865556/1930111401/0587.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89064422/1930-11-14/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01/data/sn89064422/00542865556/1930111401/0587.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01:data:sn89064422:00542865556:1930111401:0584/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01/data/sn89064422/00542865556/1930111401/0587.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89064422/1930-11-14/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01/data/sn89064422/00542865556/1930111401/0587.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89064422/1930-11-14/ed-1/?sp=4"], "batch": ["mnhi_katherine_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/minnesota/", "2/united states/minnesota/goodhue/", "3/united states/minnesota/goodhue/red wing/"], "contributor": ["minnesota historical society; saint paul, mn"], "date": "1930-11-14", "dates": ["1930-11-14"], "description": ["GE FOUR EDITORIAL EXPRESSIONS THE ORGANIZED FARMER Member tional Editorial Association Published Every Friday at 524 Plum Street Red Wing Minnesota Entered as second class mail matter at the post ffice at Red Wing Minnesota under the Act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 a year payable in advance Advertising rates on application MILDRED C SCHERF PUBLISHER F H SHOEMAKER EDITOR MANAGER Prices paid for milk to farmers is like ev erything else down If a thoughtful merch ant would only stop to think he would vote and work with and for the very farmer who is his best customer If he could only see that the price of milk in this community has fal len off about SIOOOO per month or 120000 per year which is some money Still the av erage merchant will work with the very ene mies of the farmers who are largely respon sible for the condition that robs Red Wing merchants out SIOOOO in business ev ery month This 120000 is no longer flowing through the business channels of Red Wing It is no Longer being placed in banks to be reloaned to others for the purpose of rebuilding and building up this community"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-07-10T21:58:24.669Z", "group": ["ndnp/mnhi", "minnesota-historical-society-saint-paul-mn-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89064422/1930-11-14/ed-1/?sp=4", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01:data:sn89064422:00542865556:1930111401:0587/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=298&w=219", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_katherine_ver01:data:sn89064422:00542865556:1930111401:0587/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=596&w=438", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_ka